title: Grateful Dead Live at State Fairgrounds on 1980-09-06
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Far From Me, Little Red Rooster, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Promised Land

Set 2

Shakedown Street, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance, Althea, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> The Wheel-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Sugar Magnolia, E:One More Saturday Night-> E: Brokedown Palace

Roy Bucanan then Levon Helm Opened

reviews.review_text:
I like it As good as any other recording out there for this show. I so wish I had been on tour 2 years before this. I would love to have had this during the time I knew everyone on tour. instead I was a newbe only dozen or so under my belt. still in awe of the scene back then wondering how do these people all know each other.
 The sound here has a few moments of distortion during rhythm devils but many do so it gets 5 stars because it is one AMAZING show in the history of this band .
 Almost every show put up by these guys sounds this good. Lucky bastards cause they had the tapes when we did not yet. back when we traded by mail. snail mail to boot

thanks! thanks for getting this  uploaded near the anniversary ....still one of my fav experiences @ a GD show...amazing sunset while they were performing in set # one....set#2 is off the  charts... peace
